overview: The user wanted to add database functionality and an admin dashboard
  to a sleep questionnaire application based on a provided Statement of Work.
  The agent evaluated the existing codebase, which already had the questionnaire
  logic and PDF generation. Key missing pieces were database storage for
  responses, CSV export, and an admin interface with authentication. The agent
  clarified with the user to implement a simple password-based authentication
  and to combine demographic data fields from the SOW and the existing form. The
  implementation involved updating the Prisma schema for
  , creating API endpoints for saving, retrieving, and
  exporting data, building a basic login page and an admin dashboard, and
  integrating the database save into the questionnaire submission flow. The
  solution leverages NeonDB with Prisma, providing a robust yet simple database
  backend.
